  <prompt>Add a new subsection to `docs/guides/redis-cache-azure-setup.md` §6 documenting the per-env OIDC service-principal provisioning procedure: 3 distinct SPs each scoped to a single env's KV + Redis + App Service. A compromised prod SP MUST NOT be able to rotate dev. Provide the exact `az role assignment` commands the operator runs.</prompt>
  <role>Technical writer with Azure RBAC + GitHub Actions OIDC familiarity. Apply `task-execute` skill at MINIMAL rigor.</role>
  <goal>New §6.x subsection in redis-cache-azure-setup.md showing: SP creation, federated identity credential setup against each GitHub Environment, role assignments (Key Vault Secrets Officer on env-specific KV; redis-cache-contributor or equivalent on env-specific Redis; App Service contributor on env-specific App Service), verification commands.</goal>
  <context>
    <background>Spec FR-09 + §Dependencies §External Dependencies: operator must provision 3 SPs BEFORE Theme B crons are enabled. R2 documents the procedure; does not provision (out of scope — Azure-side IAM work).</background>
